FBIS3-37706 "drsov035_a_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Yeltsin, Clinton Discuss Bosnia on Phone LD2002205694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2021 GMT 20 Feb 94 LD2002205694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, 20 Feb -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin telephoned U.S. President Bill Clinton. Vyacheslav Kostikov, the Russian president's press secretary, said that they discussed problems pertaining to the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. As a result of the conversation, an accord was reached on postponing bombing, taking into account the recent Russian diplomacy. The U.S. President highly assessed Boris Yeltsin's political initiative, which made it possible to ease significantly the crisis around Sarajevo. In the course of the telephone conversation, it was confirmed that decisions stemming from the development of the situation around Sarajevo would be adopted through UN mediation. It was agreed to continue consultations on the settlement of the situation in Bosnia in the upcoming days.
